<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2005</DATELINE><TITLE>Role of Microglia and Macrophages in Eae</TITLE><BODY>Microglia and macrophages are related cell types that play an important role in the pathogenesis of MS and EAE. This chapters reviews the role of these cells in the normal brain and their contribution to inflammatory demyelinating disease, including their role in antigen presentation, co-stimulation, and production of cytokines and other inflammatory mediators&#3;</BODY></TEXT>